    "Changes in prediction performance between KO and DO/noKO networks across LC types were relatively small, suggesting changes in behavior were subtle, consistent with overall mean changes in behavior (Extended Data Fig. 1).",
    "In addition, R 2 may change little for large second-order changes in behavior, such as variance (Extended Data Fig. 2g, leftmost dots).",
    "We confirmed in Fig. 1g-h and Extended Data Fig.",
    "4 that the KO network accurately predicted mean changes in behavior better than DO and noKO networks.",
    "We note that R 2 values for movement (left column, R 2 ≈ 0.5 for forward velocity, R 2 ≈ 0.15 for lateral and angular velocity) were not close to 1 because we predict rapid changes to movement variables frame-to-frame (with a frame rate of 30 Hz)."
